// Ballerina programs operate on a universe of values and each value belongs to only one basic type
// such as `int`, `boolean`, `map`, `record`, `function` etc. There are four kinds of values
// corresponding to four kinds of basic types. They are simple values (e.g., `int`, `float`, `boolean`),
// sequence values (e.g., `string`, `xml`), structured values (e.g., `record`, `map`, `array`), and 
// behavioral values (e.g., `function`, `object`). Simple values belong to one of the simple basic 
// types, namely `nil`, `boolean`, `int`, `float`, and `decimal`.
